list_variables.description: Key-value pairs defining configuration options for this environment. These                   options override the values that are defined in the solution stack or the                   configuration template. If you remove any options during a stack update, the                   removed options revert to default values.
list_variables.name: OptionSettings

variables.description: The name of the application that is associated with this environment.
variables.name: ApplicationName

variables.description: A prefix for your Elastic Beanstalk environment URL.
variables.name: CNAMEPrefix

variables.description: A description that helps you identify this environment.
variables.name: Description

variables.description: A name for the Elastic Beanstalk environment. If you don't specify a name, AWS CloudFormation generates                   a unique physical ID and uses that ID for the environment name. For more                   information, see Name Type.
variables.name: EnvironmentName

variables.description: The name of an Elastic Beanstalk solution stack that this configuration will use. For more                   information, see Supported                      Platforms in the AWS Elastic Beanstalk Developer Guide. You must                   specify either this parameter or an Elastic Beanstalk configuration template name.
variables.name: SolutionStackName

variables.description: An arbitrary set of tags (key-value pairs) for this environment.
variables.name: Tags

variables.description: The name of the Elastic Beanstalk configuration template to use with the environment. You                   must specify either this parameter or a solution stack name.
variables.name: TemplateName

variables.description: Specifies the tier to use in creating this environment. The environment tier                   that you choose determines whether Elastic Beanstalk provisions resources to support a web                   application that handles HTTP(S) requests or a web application that handles                   background-processing tasks.
variables.name: Tier
variables.type: Elastic Beanstalk Environment Tier Property       Type

variables.description: The version to associate with the environment.
variables.name: VersionLabel

variables.description: The URL to the load balancer for this environment.
variables.name: EndpointURL
